race.comment: ODAKA (10) good filly who indicated a win was imminent when a respectable fourth over 1350m at Beaumont (Newcastle). Can stalk the good tempo from the inside gate and finish over the top of them. BELLEVUE (5) resumed for his second prep with a fading fifth to The Little General over 1300m at Hawkesbury. Should progress from that run and the cross-over nose band goes on. Expected to take a hand in the finish. LINDA'S PRINCESS (9) six-start filly who ran a much better race when second over 1350m at Beaumont (Newcastle). Gets a better set-up for this with senior rider engaged. MAXIMUM RIDE (3) come here in peak condition fourth-up and placed at the track. Worked hard early from the sticky draw when a fading fifth over 1300m at Wyong. Worth thought.
